---

<Layout title="VCG Mechanism — Clarke 1971, Groves 1973" favicon="💎">
  <main>

    <a href="/reading/auction-theory/" class="text-sm mb-4 inline-block">&larr; back to Auction Theory</a>

    <h1>VCG Mechanism</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">Clarke 1971 &middot; Groves 1973 &middot; <a href="https://doi.org/10.2307/1914085">Clarke doi:10.2307/1914085</a> &middot; <a href="https://doi.org/10.2307/1914085">Groves doi:10.2307/1914085</a></p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">Each winner pays the <strong>externality</strong> they impose on other bidders. This makes truthful bidding dominant, allocation efficient, and participation individually rational.</p>
    </div>

    <h3>The externality principle</h3>
    <p>Your VCG payment = the total value others would have gotten without you, minus the total value others actually get. You pay exactly the harm your presence causes.</p>

    <!-- SVG: Three bidders, payment = social welfare without you minus social welfare with you -->
    <div class="flex justify-center my-6">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 500 200" class="w-full max-w-lg" style="font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;">
        <!-- World WITH bidder i -->
        <text x="130" y="18" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="11" fill-opacity="0.6">With you</text>
        <rect x="30" y="25" width="200" height="80" rx="6" fill="#a1a1aa" fill-opacity="0.15" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1"/>
        <text x="60" y="50" fill="#4ade80" font-size="11">A: $10</text>
        <text x="60" y="70" fill="currentColor" font-size="11">B: $7</text>
        <text x="60" y="90" fill="currentColor" font-size="11">C: $4</text>
        <text x="170" y="50" fill="#4ade80" font-size="10">wins item</text>
        <text x="170" y="70" fill="currentColor" font-size="10" fill-opacity="0.5">others get $11</text>

        <!-- World WITHOUT bidder i -->
        <text x="380" y="18" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="11" fill-opacity="0.6">Without you</text>
        <rect x="280" y="25" width="200" height="80" rx="6" fill="#a1a1aa" fill-opacity="0.15" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1"/>
        <text x="310" y="50" fill="currentColor" font-size="11" fill-opacity="0.4">A: gone</text>
        <text x="310" y="70" fill="#60a5fa" font-size="11">B: $7</text>
        <text x="310" y="90" fill="currentColor" font-size="11">C: $4</text>
        <text x="420" y="70" fill="#60a5fa" font-size="10">wins item</text>
        <text x="420" y="90" fill="currentColor" font-size="10" fill-opacity="0.5">others get $4</text>

        <!-- Payment calculation -->
        <rect x="100" y="125" width="300" height="55" rx="6" fill="#3b82f6" fill-opacity="0.08" stroke="#3b82f6" stroke-width="1.2"/>
        <text x="250" y="148" text-anchor="middle" fill="#60a5fa" font-size="12">A's payment = ($7 + $4) - ($7 + $4) = $7</text>
        <text x="250" y="168" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="10" fill-opacity="0.5">others' welfare without A ($11) minus others' welfare with A ($4) = $7</text>
      </svg>
    </div>

    <SchemeRepl client:visible initialCode={`; VCG mechanism: each winner pays the externality they impose
; payment_i = welfare_others_without_i - welfare_others_with_i

(define (sum lst) (if (null? lst) 0 (+ (car lst) (sum (cdr lst)))))

(define (remove-nth lst n)
  (if (= n 0) (cdr lst)
      (cons (car lst) (remove-nth (cdr lst) (- n 1)))))

(define (vcg-payment bids winner-idx)
  (let* ((others-with (remove-nth bids winner-idx))
         (welfare-others-with (sum others-with))
         ;; Without winner, next highest gets the item
         (others-without (remove-nth bids winner-idx))
         (welfare-others-without (+ (apply max others-without)
                                     (sum (cdr (sort others-without >))))))
    ;; Simplified: for single-item, payment = second-highest bid
    (apply max others-with)))

; Single item auction: bids = (10 7 4)
(define bids '(10 7 4))
(display "Bids: ") (display bids) (newline)
(display "Winner: bidder 0 (bid $10)") (newline)
(display "VCG payment: $")
(display (vcg-payment bids 0)) (newline)
(display "Surplus: $")
(display (- 10 (vcg-payment bids 0)))
; For a single item, VCG reduces to second-price (Vickrey)
`} />

    <div class="python-block my-2" style="display:none">
      <Repl client:visible initialCode={`# VCG mechanism — single item
def vcg_single_item(bids):
    """For one item: winner pays second-highest bid (= Vickrey)."""
    s = sorted(bids, reverse=True)
    winner_value = s[0]
    payment = s[1]  # externality = what second-place loses
    return dict(winner=winner_value, payment=payment,
            surplus=winner_value - payment)

print(vcg_single_item([10, 7, 4]))

# Multi-item VCG
def vcg_multi(values, k):
    """k items, unit demand. Each winner pays externality."""
    s = sorted(values, reverse=True)
    winners = s[:k]
    payments = []
    for i in range(k):
        # Without winner i, the k-th highest bid would win
        without = sorted([v for j,v in enumerate(values) if j != i], reverse=True)
        welfare_without = sum(without[:k])
        welfare_with = sum(s[:k]) - s[i]  # others' share with i present
        payments.append(welfare_without - welfare_with)
    return dict(winners=winners, payments=payments)

print(vcg_multi([10, 7, 4, 3, 1], k=2))
`} />
    </div>

    <h3>Three properties</h3>
    <p><strong>Truthful</strong>: bidding your true value is a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dominant_strategy"><img src="/reading/wikipedia.svg" alt="wp" style="display:inline;height:1em;vertical-align:-0.1em;margin-right:0.2em;"/>dominant strategy</a>. <strong>Efficient</strong>: items go to those who value them most. <strong>Individually rational</strong>: every participant is at least as well off as not participating. These three properties make VCG the theoretical backbone of <a href="https://june.kim/vector-space"><img src="/reading/jk.png" alt="jk" style="display:inline;height:1em;vertical-align:-0.1em;margin-right:0.2em;"/>embedding-space ad auctions</a>, where truthfulness matters because advertisers bid continuously without room to iterate.</p>

